### Hadith 2:625

*Narrated Nafi':*

Whenever Ibn 'Umar intended to go to Mecca he used to oil himself with a
sort of oil that had no pleasant smell, then he would go to the Mosque
of Al-Hulaita and offer the prayer, and then ride. When he mounted well
on his Mount and the Mount stood up straight, he would proclaim the
intention of assuming Ihram, and he used to say that he had seen the
Prophet doing the same.

